<Content>Fantastic Hotel The Courtyard by Mariott Hong Kong is truly a fantastic hotel. I checked with the kiosk upon arriving at the Hong Kong airport and they gave me transportation options, including a hotel shuttle (approx $150 HKD) or the express airport bus or train. I chose the train, then took a taxi to the hotel. I was rapidly checked in, and led to my room, and the bellman explained the hotel only opened in April. It could have just opened yesterday as good as it looked.The rooms are small, but efficient, with tons of storage space. The showers are unique, and the overall feeling is modern stylish. There are such minor touches as putting your name on the television screen when you turn it on, to a plug for your mp3 player to send the signal to the television. The views are very good, except for Victoria Peak which is blocked by a large building (though very high floors may have a better view.) I was on the 28th floor.Amenities are overflowing, including robes, slippers, in-room safe, and all of the desired toiletries *except* Q-tips.If I return to Hong Kong, I will definitely consider this hotel...the only drawback is that it is removed somewhat from the central area. It is a 5-minute, $3-$5 USD taxi ride to the IFC however and the city is easily accessible from that point. 
